item.title: Musing
item.description: 🍵 May 27, 2020 “Because it’s the thought of Mecca that keeps me alive. That’s what helps me face these days that are all the same, these mute crystals on the shelves, and lunch and dinner at that same horrible cafe. I’m afraid that if my dream is realized, I’ll have no reason to go on living.” — Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist 🍵 May 4, 2020

item.title: About
item.description: Hi, I’m currently a Software Engineer at Zalo working as a backend engineer. I studied Computer Science at the Ho Chi Minh City University of Technology. I have a thrist for knowledge and learning new things. Feel free to drop me a message if you want to know more about me. 😜 Personal I love making new friends with people around the world 📬; photography 📷; reading books 📚; listening to instrumental music 🎹; running 🏃; inline skating 🛼
